### 7-Day Workout Plan

| Day       | Activity                                   | Details                                        |
|-----------|--------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| **Day 1** | Strength Training                          | Warm-up: 5-10 min<br> - Squats: 3 × 12<br> - Deadlifts: 3 × 10<br> - Bench Press: 3 × 12<br> - Bent-over Rows: 3 × 12<br> - Plank: 3 × 30 sec<br> Optional Cardio: 20 min boxing<br> Cool-down: Stretching |
| **Day 2** | Active Recovery                            | Light yoga or stretching for 20-30 minutes   |
| **Day 3** | Strength Training                          | Warm-up: 5-10 min<br> - Lunges: 3 × 12 (per leg)<br> - Overhead Press: 3 × 10<br> - Pull-ups or Assisted Pull-ups: 3 × 8<br> - Bicycle Crunches: 3 × 15<br> Optional Cardio: 20 min boxing<br> Cool-down: Stretching |
| **Day 4** | Rest                                       | Day off                                      |
| **Day 5** | Full Body Workout                          | Warm-up: 5-10 min<br> - Goblet Squats: 3 × 12<br> - Push-ups: 3 × 10<br> - Kettlebell Swings: 3 × 15<br> - Mountain Climbers: 3 × 30 sec<br> Optional Cardio: 20 min boxing<br> Cool-down: Stretching |
| **Day 6** | Rest or Light Activity                     | Optional light cardio (walking, cycling)     |
| **Day 7** | High-Intensity Boxing/Cardio              | 1 hour of intense boxing/cardio session      |

### Tips
- Stay consistent with your workout schedule to see results.
- Focus on maintaining proper form during exercises to avoid injuries.
- Incorporate hydration and a balanced diet to support your weight loss goals.
